act record membership remains in\n`TurnDetail`.\n\n`TurnDetail` is the authoritative observation object. It contains exact record\nmembership plus the environment snapshot and should be stored as a JSON string\nvalue written through `MetaEdit::SetValue`.\n\n## V1 Implementation Checklist\n\n1. Bump the pinned `git-meta-lib` dependency to an exact revision containing\n   `MetaEdit::SetVa\n[TRUNCATED]\ncript records, record hashes,\n   turn summary, turn detail, and branch/review/change index memberships in one\n   logical GitMeta `apply_edits` batch.\n10. Add optional enrichment for failed/partial environment snapshots without\n    creating transcriptless turns.\n11. Add focused capture tests for first backfill, incremental capture,\n    idempotency, previous-turn linking, failed environment snapshots,\n    enrichment, and index writes.\n12. Add read/query work after the capture shape is stable: session timeline,\n    index lookup, candidate verification against turn detail, conservative\n    scoring, and reason output.\n\nSuggested build passes:\n\n1. **Storage pass:** bump `git-meta-lib`, refactor capture/dedupe to return\n   ordered `accepted_records`, add `TurnSummary` and `TurnDetail` storage without\n   environment snapshots, move capture metadata writes into one `apply_edits`\n   batch, and add `previous_turn_key`, idempotency, and first/incremental capture\n   tests. Stop and review after this pass.\n2. **Environment pass:** add best-effort environment snapshot collection behind\n   an adapter, including worktree paths and stack/branch/commit observations.\n3. **Index pass:** add branch/review/change index writes derived from\n   `observed_targets`.\n4. **Read/scoring pass:** add the first read/query shape, candidate\n   verification, conservative scoring, and reason output.\n\n## Implementation Simplification\n\nThe capture flow should use one ordered `accepted_records` result from dedupe:\n\n- record hashes answer \"have we stored this transcript record bef